==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pudder
<hw>Pud"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Puddered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Puddering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Pother</er>.]</ety> <def>To make a tumult or bustle; to splash; to
make a pother or fuss; to potter; to meddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Puddering</qex> in the designs or doings of others.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Others <qex>pudder</qex> into their food with their broad
nebs.</q> <rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pudder</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pudder
<hw>Pud"der</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To perplex; to embarrass; to
confuse; to bother; <as>as, to <ex>pudder</ex> a man</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pudder</ent>⟦br⟧

